From b73ec2f9a9805413dde0b7ef44231c7eff66d111 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Cursor Agent <cursoragent@cursor.com>
Date: Sat, 4 Jul 2026 16:34:30 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] feat(eve): hydrate video/audio attachments inline for models
 that accept them
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Attachment hydration re-inlines staged file parts through a hard whitelist
(images ≤3 MiB, PDFs ≤20 MiB); every other media type silently degrades to
an 'Attached file …' text stub — including video/audio sent to a Gemini
model that natively understands them.

Widen the inline decision per model family, mirroring detectPromptCachePath:
detectModelMediaSupport classifies the resolved model (gateway id string,
gateway instance, or direct provider instance) and hydration inlines
video/* and audio/* up to 20 MiB for the google family only. Anthropic's
converter throws UnsupportedFunctionalityError on such parts (which would
fail the whole model call) and OpenAI's input_audio path only works on its
audio-preview subset, so both stay on the text-stub path. Default behavior
is unchanged when no model is passed.

Verified: unit + integration suites, guard:invariants, lint, typecheck.
Signed-off-by: Cursor Agent <cursoragent@cursor.com>
